The paper discusses a method for assessing the overall quality of scientific papers in a particular field of study, specifically in the computer science domain. The use of corpus linguistics technique and the creation of a large corpus consisting of papers from high impact conferences suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL).
